main event: A bright object was observed striking the water and making a low arc before sinking below the horizon on November 7, 1959.
interesting points: The object was visible for about twenty to thirty seconds,The object emitted at least three flashes,It was seen by three reputable witnesses,The incident was reported to Air Force headquarters for further information,Investigation concluded that the witnesses may have seen a meteor rather than a craft.
location: North of Hawaiian Islands, Hawaii, USA
